Description: Rim and body fragment of very large North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos, made up of two non-joining sets of nine and two fragments. Generally worn to very worn. Inside reserved; maeander band on top of rim; animal frieze on shoulder, above worn area, with much filling ornament and added red; from left, lion to left, swans facing across a floral, lions facing across a floral , uncertain remains. Incised inscription on rim.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 65, no. 784, pl. XXI, no. 784)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 685, no. 435)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1136)
